  "code_review": {
    "status": "pass",
    "findings_fixed": [
      "Cross-hart scheduler decision is a thin semantic evidence object instead of expanding the local SchedulerDecision record into an overloaded cross-hart state machine",
      "Command preflight requires exact deciding and target hart generations at decision time",
      "Target queue ownership is checked against the target hart identity and recorded separately from the current target hart generation",
      "Target hart event attribution is checked against the selected activation generation instead of accepting any target-hart-only attribution",
      "History graph edges are historical attribution edges, not live queue or activation ownership",
      "osctl ViewV1 uses explicit id/generation references rather than raw internal record dumps"
    ],
